Steps.Message: Update at 20:05 - We're very sorry we've had to switch off your electricity. Our engineers have turned off the power in the Haywards Heath area for safety so they can investigate reports of an overhead line on the ground. Our estimated time to have your power back on is between 22:30 and 23:30. If you'd like more information about why we sometimes have to switch power off to work; here's a short video https://bit.ly/3cYez0V. We'll keep you updated with progress.

We became aware of this power cut at 19:49. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically
